comment: Singler (OKC) legally contests Harden's (OKC) jumpshot.
Kanter (OKC) sets the screen on Ariza (HOU) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Howard (HOU) maintains legal guarding position. Contact with Westbrook (OKC) is incidental to his attempt to guard his layup.
Harden (HOU) does not dislodge Waiters (OKC) prior to securing the offensive rebound.
Singler (OKC) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Brewer's (HOU) transition layup attempt.
Westbrook (OKC) commits a take foul on Howard (HOU).
Westbrook (OKC) dislodges Brewer (HOU), causing him to land OOB while trying to secure the rebound.
Kanter (OKC) sets the screen on Brewer (HOU) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Waiters (OKC) does not affect Harden's (HOU) RSBQ at the start of his drive.
Harden (HOU) makes body contact with Westbrook (OKC) that affects his RSBQ in transition.

An inadvertant whistle is blown (a whistle that is erroneously sounded by a referee when no call is made on the play). This results in a jump ball at center circle between any two players in the game at the time of the whistle.
Morrow (OKC) commits a take foul on Terry (HOU) that causes him to step OOB.
Westbrook (OKC) commits a take foul on Terry (HOU).
Kanter (OKC) makes incidental contact and does not dislodge Smith (HOU) or affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Westbrook (OKC) makes contact with Ariza's (HOU) body and arms that affects his ability to cleanly catch the inbounds pass.
Howard (HOU) legally contests Westbrook's (OKC) jump shot.
Morrow (OKC) switches his pivot foot.
Westbrook (OKC) commits a take foul on Brewer (HOU).
Brewer (HOU) attempts to take a foul on Westbrook (OKC) but cleanly knocks the ball away.
Ariza (HOU) clamps Kanter's (OKC) arm and the contact affects his ability to get the rebound.
